[Fibropapillomatosis is a neoplastic disease putatively caused by a chelonid fibropapilloma-associated herpesvirus (CFPHV). This virus has been documented to infect all sea turtle species.

Around the world, the prevalences of infected green turtles vary considerably, but most populations contain at least a few CFPHV infected individuals.

The infection has also been documented in healthy turtles, so there may be environmental factors that contribute to the development of the tumors. Anthropogenic stressors such as pollutants may be implicated. - Mod.PMB

Maps of Australia can be seen at http://maps.unomaha.edu/peterson/funda/MapLinks/Australia/Australia_files/image001.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4311783,53916. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
